Meal Plans and Assistance - St. Jude Children’s Research Hospital Meal Plans and Assistance - St. Jude Children’s Research Hospital Meal Plans and Assistance - St. Jude Children’s Research Hospital Meal Plans and Assistance - St. Jude Children’s Research Hospital St. Judewill provide meal assistance either through issuing aSt. Judemeal account or  aSt. Jude-issued reloadable debit card under the following terms:
St. Judemeal accounts are available to allSt. Judepatients and their caregivers for use in theSt. Judecafeterias by providing the patient’s medical record number (MRN) to the cashier.St. Judemeal accounts are also available to guests of the patient as long as the guest is permitted to be in the hospital. The meal account will be loaded when the patient is atSt. Judefor treatment. Unspent funds will roll off each day at midnight.

Meal Plans and Assistance - St. Jude Children’s Research Hospital Meal Plans and Assistance - St. Jude Children’s Research Hospital Meal Plans and Assistance - St. Jude Children’s Research Hospital Meal Plans and Assistance - St. Jude Children’s Research Hospital Debit Cards for meals will be issued to all patients inSt. Judeowned or sponsored lodging and toSt. Judepatients in patient-provided lodging while the patient has scheduled treatment atSt. Jude. The weekly allowance loaded to the debit card may be prorated based on the number of days the patient is inSt. Judelodging or based on the treatment schedule for those in patient-provided housing.
St. Judewill provide meal assistance on a debit card to non-cohabitating parents, guardians or caregivers.  Funds will be loaded on the debit card during the time when the patient has scheduled treatment atSt. Jude.
